    <a class="nav-link" href="#Loops">Loops</a>
  </nav>

  <main id="main-doc">
    <section class="main-section" id="Introduction">
      <header>Introduction</header>
      <p>JavaScript is a versatile programming language used to create interactive websites.</p>
      <p>It runs in the browser and allows dynamic content changes.</p>
      <p>It can also be used on the server side via Node.js.</p>
      <p>JavaScript is one of the core technologies of the web.</p>
      <p>It supports object-oriented, imperative, and functional styles.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="main-section" id="Getting_Started">
      <header>Getting Started</header>
      <p>To get started, you just need a text editor and a browser.</p>
      <p>You can include JavaScript directly in an HTML file using the <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> tag.</p>
      <pre><code>&lt;script&gt;
  alert("Hello World!");
&lt;/script&gt;
</code></pre>
      <p>Modern browsers have built-in developer tools for testing JavaScript.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="main-section" id="Variables_and_Data_Types">
      <header>Variables and Data Types</header>
      <p>You can declare variables using <code>let</code>, <code>const</code>, or <code>var</code>.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><code>let</code> is block-scoped and reassignable.</li>
        <li><code>const</code> is block-scoped and not reassignable.</li>
        <li><code>var</code> is function-scoped (legacy).</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Common data types include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>String</li>
        <li>Number</li>
        <li>Boolean</li>
        <li>Object</li>
        <li>Array</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="main-section" id="Functions">
      <header>Functions</header>
      <p>Functions are reusable blocks of code that perform a task.</p>
      <pre><code>function greet(name) {
  return "Hello " + name;
}</code></pre>
      <p>You can call a function by its name followed by parentheses.</p>
      <p>Functions can accept parameters and return values.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="main-section" id="Loops">
      <header>Loops</header>
      <p>Loops are used to repeat code multiple times.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><code>for</code> loop</li>
        <li><code>while</code> loop</li>
        <li><code>do...while</code> loop</li>
      </ul>
      <pre><code>for (let i = 0; i &lt; 5; i++) {
  console.log(i);
}</code></pre>
      <p>Loops help when you need to iterate over data structures like arrays.</p>
    </section>
  </main>
</body>
</html>

